text: West Achaea ( – Dytiki Achaia) is a municipality in the Achaea regional unit, West Greece region, Greece. The seat of the municipality is the town Kato Achaia.Kallikratis law Greece Ministry of Interior The municipality has an area of 573.30 km2. ==Municipality== The municipality West Achaea was formed at the 2011 local government reform by the merger of the following 4 former municipalities, that became municipal units: *Dymi *Larissos *Movri *Olenia ==References== Category:Municipalities of Western Greece Category:Populated places in Achaea
title: West Achaea
